(325, 'Meeting Prep — 2026-03-02: **Source: **DocSend deck + email pre-read from raj@withorbi.com (Mar 2, 2026) **Deck: **[https://docsend.com/view/y3wrtejc6wv8kem4](https://docsend.com/view/y3wrtejc6wv8kem4) ### Traction - 1,110+ invite-only beta users - 30% WoW growth (Nov-Jan) - 60% M1 retention (best cohorts: 80%) - 26 min avg session (2.5x Roblox), max 6 hrs/week - 50% referral rate ### Market - US 5-12: 30M kids × $123 ARPU = $3.7B/yr - Global: 1.2B+ digital-native kids × $60 = $70B+/yr - AI companions: $37B (2025) → $552B (2035), 31% CAGR ### GTM - Homeschooling networks (VELA, Primer, National Microschooling Center) - App Store waitlist: 3K+ | Parent influencers: 10K+ | Gaming creators: 50K+ - Monetization: microtransactions + subscriptions ### Raise $2M seed. Roadmap: Phase 1 digital worlds → Phase 2 cross-app (Minecraft, YouTube) → Phase 3 offline (toys, wearables) ### Key Questions 1. Safety & regulatory: COPPA, Character.AI lawsuits, content moderation framework? 1. Valuation & DeVC fit: $2M raise at what val? Where does $30-150K cheque fit? 1. FrontRow post-mortem: same team, what failed, what''s different? 1. Retention depth: M3/M6 curves? Novelty decay risk in kids products? 1. Unit economics: inference cost per session? Can microtx + subs cover it? 1. Roblox defense: what if Roblox adds AI companions? ---
AI notes: ### Founder Backgrounds - **Raj** leads growth at Hobby; previously taught sports, arts, and math to kids in a government school in India starting at age 1...'),
(327, 'Rajat - Follow-up Call Request - 2026-02-26: Rajat requesting follow-up call with Aakash and Rahul after initial call with Raj Singh (CEO). Sneha to set up - Raj is based in the US. --- PRE-READ FROM RAJ (24 Feb 2026): PRODUCT DEMO & SESSION RECORDINGS SHARED: 1. Product demo video - Video link provided 2. Session recordings to show core user behaviors: SESSION #1 - Emma, 10 yo | 45 mins session | 2 days ago TLDR Insights: - Treats her pet "Whiskers" like a living being with needs, engaging in care-taking activities like making soup and visiting the vet when her cat is sick - Invents mini-games and activities to do together (playing fetch, painting, learning to spell) - KEY QUOTES: "You are my favourite part of the day." "I can do this all day and night." SESSION #2 - Freddy, 9 yo | 1 Hour 31 mins | Today | M2 cohort TLDR Insights: - Even in month 2, Freddy is still highly engaged, his storylines are richly detailed, unusually specific about the world, characters, and micro-details - Brings all his favourite characters like Sonic to life, creates adventure storyline with them and his pet --- ORIGINAL PRE-READ (23 Feb 2026): COMPANY OVERVIEW: Orbi is building AI companions for kids designed for play, learning, and social connection. Kids are skipping Roblox to create social worlds with their companions, spending up to 4 hours per day. TRACTION: - Beta with 1000+ kids - Growing 30% WoW - 60% M1 retention TEAM: 1. Raj (CEO) - Led growth for India''s first alt-tech university from...'),
(329, 'Key Metrics & Product: - YC W26 batch | 4 employees | HQ: 311 California St, San Francisco - Axis outperforms Google DeepMind''s AlphaGenome by 6.7% on regulatory element binding prediction - Building largest proprietary dataset of millions of experimentally validated regulatory DNA sequences - 72% sequence diversity — generated sequences explore genuinely novel design space - Wet lab + AI — currently testing sequences in lab to validate
RM notes: - Yash raised money from Contrary Capital - Started at end of 2024 - Dropped out of college - Released first model in October before YC - Encode data set - Scientific Advisor - Dr. Manolis Kellis — Professor of CS, MIT + Broad Institute (regulatory genomics) - Keen to connect Onco data in India - Mass of data available - Raised $3M funding to date - Signing LOIs from hospitals - Targeting 3-5 LOIs - BOM hospital is pending ethics committees - CloudNine
